<caption id="B5CB04FE8A4EFFDF7DE6BF17FEF51797" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1459474/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" startId="72.[151,255,1393,1416]" targetBox="[217,1369,1120,1372]" targetPageId="72">
<paragraph id="E10B54768A4EFFDF7DE6BF17FEF51797" blockId="72.[151,1437,1393,1800]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="D3C088648A4EFFDF7DE6BF17FEAD14B7" bold="true" box="[151,310,1393,1416]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">FIGURE 167.</emphasis>
Hybrid #158 (dorsal, ventral). Mexico: Oaxaca, Sierra Juarez, Chiltepec [San Juan Quiotepec?], 1970, leg. A. Díaz Francés (UNAM). Originally hypothesized to be an aberrant 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7ECABFF7FB8E1497" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[955,1045,1425,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Heliconius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erato">
<emphasis id="D3C088648A4EFFDF7ECABFF7FB8E1497" box="[955,1045,1425,1448]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
H. 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7EACBFF7FB8E1497" box="[989,1045,1425,1448]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="erato">erato</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by de la Maza (1991), Mallet 
<emphasis id="D3C088648A4EFFDF7814BFF7FA071497" box="[1381,1436,1424,1448]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
(2007) interpreted this specimen as an 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7F27BFD7FCA814F7" authorityName="Doubleday" authorityYear="1847" box="[598,819,1457,1480]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Heliconius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="erato" subSpecies="petiverana">
<emphasis id="D3C088648A4EFFDF7F27BFD7FCA814F7" box="[598,819,1457,1480]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7F27BFD7FD2F14F7" box="[598,692,1457,1480]" genus="H." pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="erato">
H. 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7F0DBFD7FD2F14F7" box="[636,692,1457,1480]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="erato" subSpecies="petiverana">erato</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7FB0BFD7FCA814F7" box="[705,819,1457,1480]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="petiverana">petiverana</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 168) 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7ECCBFD7FB4214F7" authorityName="Comstock &amp; Brown" authorityYear="1950" box="[957,1241,1456,1480]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Heliconius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="charithonia" subSpecies="vasquezae">
<emphasis id="D3C088648A4EFFDF7ECCBFD7FB4214F7" box="[957,1241,1456,1480]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7ECCBFD7FBC414F7" box="[957,1119,1456,1480]" genus="H." pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="charithonia">
H. 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7E92BFD6FBC414F7" box="[995,1119,1456,1480]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="charithonia" subSpecies="vasquezae">charithonia</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF791DBFD7FB4214F7" box="[1132,1241,1457,1480]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="vasquezae">vasquezae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 169) F1 or backcross to 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7C54BFB7FEE414D7" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[293,383,1489,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Heliconius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erato">
<emphasis id="D3C088648A4EFFDF7C54BFB7FEE414D7" box="[293,383,1489,1512]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
H. 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7C36BFB7FEE414D7" box="[327,383,1489,1512]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="erato">erato</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on wing shape (particularly the acute apex of the HW), the specimen is clearly not an 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF78F3BFB7FF541737" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Heliconius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erato">
<emphasis id="D3C088648A4EFFDF78F3BFB7FF541737" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
H. 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7DE6BF97FF541737" box="[151,207,1521,1544]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="erato">erato</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and there is little else to suggest that it has any genetic contribution from that species. It appears to be an aberrant 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7DE6BC77FEAC1717" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" box="[151,311,1552,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Heliconius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="charithonia">
<emphasis id="D3C088648A4EFFDF7DE6BC77FEAC1717" box="[151,311,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
H. 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF7DCABC76FEAC1717" box="[187,311,1552,1576]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="charithonia">charithonia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Note also the absence of basal red spots on the HWV, which are present in both putative parentsperhaps indicative of developmental anomalies. A recently posted image (Fig. 170) shows a 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF79F2BC57FB481777" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[1155,1235,1585,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Heliconius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sara">
<emphasis id="D3C088648A4EFFDF79F2BC57FB481777" box="[1155,1235,1585,1608]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
H. 
<taxonomicName id="26B42FF58A4EFFDF79D5BC57FB481777" box="[1188,1235,1585,1608]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="sara">sara</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a genetically modified (knockout) WntA gene, whose phenotype exhibits the loss of a large area of black pigment on the forewing. This suggests that the enlarged yellow forewing patch (or absence of black pigment) of the above hybrid could be the result of a mutation.
</paragraph>
